Comment:
The Intern(2015) Movie Review :

I like these kind of movies where you can sit back and relax. I find the emotions in humans bigger and larger than the powers of superheroes. The Intern is about a young CEO Jules played by Anne Hathaway who has given her everything to set up her e-commerce business. She has taken care of it like her child and brought it to a success within a short span. Even her husband supports her along the way by dropping out from his job and looking after their daughter. However in her hectic schedule she is not be able to spend much time with her family. Even to herself. She is missing her life and her habit of taking everything on her shoulders makes her and her company miss all the schedules. This is where her newly appointed senior intern Ben, played by Robert De Niro, shows her the way to lead her life. The bond between Ben and Jules forms the crux of the story. Ben is a 70 year old widower and a very organized old school person who has worked for 40 years in a phonebook printing office. This movie shows a clear distinction between the two generations and their work culture. And surprisingly,  the old generation seemed to have managed their work pretty well. Eventually,  Jules is able to balance her life as Ben becomes her bestfriend. The movie is of today's generation and we can completely relate it to our corporate lives. The bond between Ben and Jules has been showcased very well and both the lead actors played their roles to perfection. I loved the movie. You can watch it on playstore and I am sure it makes for a nice Sunday morning watch.

Comment:
I just returned from seeing this movie and I was very impressed! Great movie with a good balance of emotional content and great timing on the comedy. Here's a copy/paste from my fb review. I would highly recommend this movie to young and "old" alike:)

The Intern, starring Robert Deniro. Great movie!! I highly recommend it. A light hearted comedy that was well done! Robert Deniro plays a retired CEO of a once bustling phone book company, now no longer in business due to the high tech computer era. He quickly realizes he's had enough of playing shuffle board and other retirement activities, and that he misses the challenges and the focus of the working world. So he decides to answer an add for a new upstart fashion company looking to hire senior interns to gain more "old school" business perspective. He soon learns that while he may be considered "washed up" by the much younger employees of this new company..he still has a few tricks up his well pressed sleeve and quickly garners both the admiration and respect of his younger co-workers. The owner of the company played by Ann Hathaway, however, proves to be a much larger but rewarding challenge to the retired CEO.
